The Telegraph - Calcutta : Metro
 Saturday, May 29, 2004 				 Call to make audit a must
 A STAFF REPORTER																								The Institute of Company Secretaries of India is approaching the government and regulatory bodies to carve out new areas of practice, Mahesh Anant Athavale, president of the institute said on Friday during a two-day national conference of company secretaries in the city.																								We are talking with the department of company affairs and Sebi to make secretarial audit mandatory, wherein we can act as an extended arm of Sebi in the capital market, said Athavale. He urged company secretaries to include more elements in their basket of expertise.																								We change the syllabus every three years, added Athavale. The institute has over 18,000 members and around 1.5 lakh students. 
